        public static boolean oneStepDFS​(int[][] labyrint,
                                 Coordinates adj,
                                 boolean finished,
                                 int cnt)
                          throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        One step of DFS algorithm. Gets a set of open nodes, and calls itself on each one of them, until it finds a final point. If the final point has been found, it returns immediately.
        Parameters:
        labyrint - The labyrint which we run our search algorithm on
        adj - List of open nodes
        finished - Marks if the final point has been found, if yes, the value is true
        cnt - Counter of steps
        Returns:
        Returns true if the final point has been already found
